<pre class="bz_comment_text">The bug is in the function make_available_at_least (line 499).
See the following lines:

if (need_alloc &gt; context-&gt;allocated) {
    guint new_size = 1;
    while (new_size &lt; need_alloc)
        new_size *= 2;
...

new_size starts with 1 and multiplies until it is larger or equal to need_alloc. If need_alloc is larger than 2^31, new_size will become 2^31 and multiply itself in 2, and become 0. This would lead to an infinite loop.</pre>
